JO  - Management Science
SP  - 635
EP  - 646
VL  - 17
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper seeks a theoretical basis for determining the optimal parameters of the X?-chart under the specified conditions. These parameters are the sample size, the factor determining the spread of the control limits, and the intersample interval. The paper shows how to determine these parameters under sound practical assumptions so that the relevant cost function is minimized. Illustrative examples show how the formulated model can be applied.
