TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Shuttle Car Assignment Problem in the Mining Industry
AU  - Reynolds, Gary H.
Y1  - 1971/05/01
PY  - 1971
DA  - 1971/05/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.17.9.652
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.17.9.652
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 652
EP  - 655
VL  - 17
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Shuttle cars form a part of the standard equipment employed by the mining industry in the transportation of coal when using the room-and-piller method for extracting coal from underground seams. These cars are subject to frequent failure, so the problem of assigning shuttle cars to sections of the mine is considered in this paper, with the objective of maximizing expected output. A particularly simple solution is found that could be used readily by any mine foreman.
AB  - Shuttle cars form a part of the standard equipment employed by the mining industry in the transportation of coal when using the room-and-piller method for extracting coal from underground seams. These cars are subject to frequent failure, so the problem of assigning shuttle cars to sections of the mine is considered in this paper, with the objective of maximizing expected output. A particularly simple solution is found that could be used readily by any mine foreman.
